<item>
            <title>[HBASE-1293] hfile doesn&apos;t recycle decompressors</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-1293</link>
                <project id="12310753" key="HBASE">HBase</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The Compression codec stuff from hadoop has the concept of recycling compressors and decompressors - this is because a compression codec uses &quot;direct buffers&quot; which reside outside the JVM regular heap space.  There is a risk that under heavy concurrent load we could run out of that &apos;direct buffer&apos; heap space in the JVM.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;HFile does not call algorithm.returnDecompressor and returnCompressor.  We should fix that.&lt;/p&gt;


&lt;p&gt;I found this bug via OOM crashes under jdk 1.7 - it appears to be partially due to the size of my cluster (200gb, 800 regions, 19 servers) and partially due to weaknesses in JVM 1.7.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
